## 1. Delayed Repression and Emergent Instability in Adaptive Multi-Agent Systems
**arxiv_id:** 2605.30392 | **upvotes:** 1
https://huggingface.co/papers/2605.30392
**Keywords:** replicator equation, Hopf bifurcation, reinforcement learning, tabular Q-learning, center manifold reduction
**GitHub:** https://github.com/YehudaItkin/delayed-repression-instability (0 stars)
**Summary:** Delayed institutional responses can destabilize multi-agent systems through Hopf bifurcations, with learning-based agents showing greater resilience than reactive ones due to memory effects in Q-values.

## 2. One-Step Gradient Delay is Not a Barrier for Large-Scale Asynchronous Pipeline Parallel LLM Pretraining
**arxiv_id:** 2606.30634 | **upvotes:** 25
https://huggingface.co/papers/2606.30634
**Keywords:** Pipeline Parallelism, asynchronous implementations, gradient staleness, PipeDream-2BW, AdamW
**Summary:** Asynchronous pipeline parallelism with PipeDream-2BW can achieve near-synchronous performance through optimizer selection and error feedback correction, overcoming traditional stability concerns.

## 3. Timewarp: Transferable Acceleration of Molecular Dynamics by Learning
  Time-Coarsened Dynamics
**arxiv_id:** 2302.01170 | **upvotes:** 0
https://huggingface.co/papers/2302.01170
**Keywords:** normalising flow, Markov chain Monte Carlo, Boltzmann distribution, Timewarp, metastable states
**GitHub:** https://github.com/microsoft/timewarp (66 stars)
**Summary:** Timewarp, an enhanced sampling method using normalizing flows in MCMC, accelerates MD simulations by making large time steps and is transferable across different molecular systems.

## 4. Enhanced Sampling, Public Dataset and Generative Model for Drug-Protein
  Dissociation Dynamics
**arxiv_id:** 2504.18367 | **upvotes:** 0
https://huggingface.co/papers/2504.18367
